<table width="100%">
<tr>
  <td valign="top">  
  <div class="contentPadding">
  
  <div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">Make holding public office entail a sacrifice of certain rights.</div>
  <table width="100%">
  <tr>
    <td valign="top">
    <div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">michaeljcorliss</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">7 days ago</span></div>
    </td>
    <td align="right">
      





    <div>
      


      

      
        <span id="FlagIdea"><a class="iconLink" href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('FlagIdea', '/akira/flagDiscussionTopic.do?ID=2562')"><img alt="Warning" class="iconLink" src="/images/iconshock/warning_16.gif" border="0">&nbsp;Flag</a></span>
      

      

    </div>

    </td>
  </tr>
  </table>
    


  <div id="DiscussionTopicText_2562">
    





  <div style="float:left; margin:3px;">
      <div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2562">
        <div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2562', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2237&topicID=2562&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 7 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 16</div><div>Votes Against : 32</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2562'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2562" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 7 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 16</div><div>Votes Against : 32</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2562'))">-16</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2562', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2237&topicID=2562&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
      </div>  
  </div>

  


  In shaping our nation, public office holders are given the power and privilege that that task requires.  However, this power can be abused.  The risk should be minimized by making it a requirement of such offices that the office holders voluntarily sacrifice certain rights.  The obvious example would be the right to privacy: if someone is given the power to create laws, to implement policy, that person should not be able to hide how those laws affect his or her personal situation.<br/>

  <h3>Why Is This Idea Important?</h3><div>Our government is a representational democracy.  If such a government is to be open, the very lives of the representative must be open to the scrutiny of the public.  Representatives are given privileges beyond those of the average citizen, and they should thus be subject to oversight that the average citizen is protected against.</div>

  </div>

  <div style="clear:both"><div>

  <div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;">Idea # 104</span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2562"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2237">Making Government Operations More Open</a></span></div>  

  


